      <scopecontent id="aspace_5039980e9b59933b3d17cef82de05973">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>This collection consists of the biannual newsletters for the Paul Mellon Centre for Studies in British Art from the charity's inaugural issue in December 1995 to May 2017.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <bioghist id="aspace_22f33188a6dbc955ce56cf574dae0efb">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>The Paul Mellon Centre for Studies in British Art, founded in 1970, is an educational charity committed to supporting original research into the history of British art and architecture of all periods. The Centre contains an extensive library and manuscript collection, with over 12,000 books about British art. It is the sister institution to the Yale Center for British Art, with which it collaborates closely, and is part of Yale University.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <accessrestrict id="aspace_2375fc01d8e986dd95495a32a1db9f72">
         <head>Conditions Governing Access</head>
